

# MaliMate 💚 — Personal Budget Tracker

MaliMate is a personal budgeting Android application built with Kotlin, designed to help users take control of their finances in a fun and engaging way. The app combines powerful budgeting tools with gamification elements to make managing money enjoyable and rewarding.

---

## Purpose
Many people struggle to track their spending habits and maintain consistent savings goals. MaliMate solves this by providing a simple, structured, and motivating platform to monitor income, expenses, and savings — all from your Android device.

---

## Features

### Core Features
- **User Authentication** — Secure registration and login system using Room database
- **Expense Categories** — Create and manage custom spending categories
- **Expense Tracking** — Log expenses with date, time, description, category and optional photo
- **Expense Search** — Filter and view expenses by date range
- **Category Spending Totals** — View total spending per category over a selected period
- **Monthly Spending Goals** — Set minimum and maximum monthly spending targets
- **Spending Graph** — Visual bar chart showing spending per category against goals
- **Firebase Integration** — Data stored securely in an online Firebase database

### Own Features
- **Gamification System** — Earn points and unlock badges by logging transactions and achieving savings goals. Progress through levels from Beginner to MaliMate Champion
- **Savings Goals Tracker** — Create named savings goals with target amounts, make contributions, and track progress visually. Completing a goal awards bonus gamification points

---

## Tech Stack
- **Language:** Kotlin
- **Database:** Room DB (local) + Firebase Realtime Database (online)
- **Architecture:** Activity-based with DAO pattern
- **Charts:** MPAndroidChart
- **Min SDK:** 24
- **Target SDK:** 36

